The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 PC singles out Bihar

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Feb. 28: Bihar, which sends 40 members to the Lok Sabha, found special mention in P. Chidambaram?s budget speech today.

 The United Progressive Alliance government has formulated for the state a special plan for implementation under the Rashtriya Sam Vikas Yojana with 100 per cent central assistance to bring about improvement in sectors like power, road connectivity, irrigation, horticulture, forestry and watershed development.

 Chidambaram said Bihar has also been identified as one of the few states that needs special grants in health and education.

 Seven projects worth Rs 2,531.35 crore have been identified for implementation during the Tenth Plan and Rs 621.56 crore have been released for project costs and preparing detailed reports. Central assistance at the rate of Rs 1,000 crore a year will be made available during the plan period subject to actual utilisation. Central agencies will be involved for timely implementation of the projects. 

 The finance minister announced that backward districts of Bihar would receive assistance from the Backward Regions Grant Fund. He said the state would also get Rs 7,975 crore by way of grants for the period 2005-10.

 Referring to the common minimum programme, which talked about special economic packages for Bihar, Jammu and Kashmir and the Northeast, the finance minister said till now Bihar has received special assistance under the Rashtriya Sam Vikas Yojana.

 ?I may also point out that recognising the needs of Bihar, the Tenth Finance Commission has made substantial grants amounting to Rs 7,975 crore for the period 2005-10,? he added.

 When the NDA was in power, Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee had offered a package clubbing various projects such as a thermal power station at Barh, a railway wagon factory at Harnaut (both fall in Nitish Kumar?s constituency), an ordnance factory in Rajgir (in George Fernandes?s constituency) besides the national highway project. 




